{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectSignalName\/notify","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectsignalname\/notify"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"notify","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Case","title":"ObjectSignalName.notify","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B10SignalNameO6notifyyA2CmF","symbolKind":"case"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectSignalName"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"The notify signal is emitted on an object when one of its properties has","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its value set through "},{"code":"g_object_set_property()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"g_object_set()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", et al.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"notify","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that getting this signal doesn’t itself guarantee that the value of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"explicitNotify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then any call to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_set_property()"},{"type":"text","text":" results"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"type":"text","text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If they did pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"explicitNotify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then this signal is emitted only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when they explicitly call ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_notify()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and common practice is to do that only when the value has actually changed."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This signal is typically used to obtain change notification for a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single property, by specifying the property name as a detail in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_connect()"},{"type":"text","text":" call, like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["g_signal_connect (text_view->buffer, \"notify::paste-target-list\",","                  G_CALLBACK (gtk_text_view_target_list_notify),","                  text_view)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to note that you must use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"#class@GObject.ParamSpec#parameter-names","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"detail strings for the notify signal."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","abstract":[],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"GLibObje